    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-13T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-13T12:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/527: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-13T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 13, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. It seems probable that the Central American highway project will come up
                    early in the Conference and it is therefore desirable that <pb facs="0538"
                        n="468" xml:id="pg_468"/> I should have the Department’s instructions in
                    this connection as early as practicable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
